{"word":"ἑδνόω","slug":"ἑδνόω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἑδνόω</b></el> <el>(ἑδνόω,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἕδνον'><el>ἕδνον</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to promise for wedding-presents, to betroth</i> one's daughter, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b>:—so in <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>in <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a> also, <i>to marry</i>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}